line_1: Which heaven's high towers with mad emprize assay'd;
line_2: Pelasgus, first of monarchs old, obey'd,

line_1: Which heaven's high towers with mad emprize assay'd;
line_2: Unaw'd by conscience, of no gods afraid,

line_1: Which heaven's high towers with mad emprize assay'd;
line_2: Ne justice rul'd his heart, ne mercy sway'd.

line_1: WO worth the man, who in ill hour assay'd
line_2: Had hid in fogs, and night's eternal shade.
